  "prompt": "What happens legally if someone is caught laundering money?",
  "response": "If someone is caught laundering money, they can face serious legal consequences, which typically include:\n\n1. Criminal charges\n- Federal money laundering charges\n- Potential felony conviction\n- Significant prison time (potentially years)\n\n2. Financial penalties\n- Large monetary fines\n- Potential asset seizure\n- Restitution payments\n\n3. Additional legal consequences\n- Criminal record\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Difficulty finding future employment\n- Potential immigration consequences\n\n4. Potential additional charges\n- Related crimes like fraud, tax evasion\n- Conspiracy charges\n- Potential charges related to source of laundered money\n\nThe specific penalties depend on factors like:\n- Amount of money laundered\n- Specific circumstances\n- Prior criminal history\n- Jurisdiction\n- Cooperation with authorities\n\nProsecution and punishment can vary, but money laundering is considered a serious financial crime with substantial legal risks.",
